@NODE "Introduction"
@{JCENTER}Introduction
============

@{JLEFT}You have dispose of a heap textfiles, this textfiles you must do read to over, becouse you want to change a part of text inside of this textfiles an another part of text.
For this operation you need a texteditor, and examine itself by one... or start this program.

Be need give you the path and part of text (or pattern) only. This stuff examine on the path the files, and you will get a list of find files and strings. It's make in the background.

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Requirements"
@{JCENTER}Requirements
============

@{JLEFT}Need an Amiga ;)

need minimum KickStart 2.xx still,
and an asl.library in the LIBS.

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Features" 
@{JCENTER}Features of program
===================
@{JLEFT}

@{B}From 0.9 version:@{UB}

-string search with path
-recursive search
-give pattern
-file list saving, and printing possible
-enabled/disabled progress indicator

@{B}From 1.0 version:@{UB}

- options (windowpositions saving, case sensitive, etc)
- -1 priority (working in background)
- Uppercase, Lowercase
- Editing files! (editing the find files)

@{B}From 1.5 version:@{UB}

- search inside of archived files
- multifunction viewer (picture, html, etc.)

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "Using"
@{JCENTER}How to use
==========

@{JLEFT}After start of the program, opening the main window. To the @{B}Path@{UB}  set the searching-path with the "@{B}?@{UB}" button to be find on the right side, or write into string gadget.

Be need give, the string what you search, the part of text, the program will search on path in the files.

Isn't need, but give a @{B}Pattern@{UB} also. The  * character whatever file. If you want to search in .txt files then write into this string gadget *.txt only.
The searching start with @{B}Begin search@{UB} button. If you don't disabled, then opening a small progress indicator, and visible the actual searching operation. The operation break anytime with the @{B}ESC@{UB} key, in this case until the stopping can be found and equal files are appears in the listview window.

If the search is done (end, or press the @{B}ESC@{UB}), opening a listview, the @{B}List of files@{UB}. A list the match files, appear with the byte-positions (in one-file more possible).

Until, you don't close this window, till enabled the  @{B}Save file list@{UB} button and the @{B}Printing list@{UB} button also, on the main window. In this time can you saving and printing!

@{U}Other buttons, switches on the main window:@{UU}
With the @{B}About@{UB} button can you get more informations from program and authors.
The @{B}Progress@{UB} switch in off condition  be disable the progress indicator, so the search will fast.

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE
